Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of 
water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate 
the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}.
Roughly chop the @chives{1%bunch} (use #scissors{} if easier).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} and bring back 
to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with 
@oil{1%tbsp} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat the oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @breadcrumbs{25%g}. Season with salt and pepper and fry, 
stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}. TIP: Watch it like a 
hawk as they can burn easily. Once cooked, transfer the toasted crumbs to a 
#bowl{} and set aside.

Melt the @butter{20%g} in a saucepan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the 
shallot. Stir-fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}, then stir in the 
@plain flour{1.5%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've 
made a roux!

Gradually stir in the @water{200%ml}, followed by the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. 
Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and half the chives, then remove from the 
heat. Add the Cheddar cheese and stir until melted. Taste and season with salt 
and pepper if needed.

Add the cooked pasta to the cheese sauce and stir to combine. Add a splash of 
water to loosen if needed, then transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle 
the crumb evenly over the top.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the crumbs are golden, 
~{5-6%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from your oven and leave to stand.

== Garlicky Tenderstem® Broccoli ==

Meanwhile, clean your frying pan and pop it back on medium-high heat with a 
drizzle of oil. Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways.

Once hot, add the broccoli and stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the garlic and 
fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. 
Lower the heat to medium and allow to cook until the broccoli is tender, 
~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

Spoon the baked penne into #bowls{} and sprinkle the remaining chives over the 
top.

Serve the broccoli alongside. Enjoy!

> This Breadcrumbed Baked Mushroom Penne is a crowd pleaser and is one to get the 
> family round the dinner table for. Super simple to make, and easily customised 
> to suit the kids too!